<title type="html"><![CDATA[xpm-nes, embedding X11 xpm files in NES software]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11194&amp;p=128107#p128107"><![CDATA[
Hi, there's a NES demo for making xpm available in NES programs. Basically an xpm file is for coming into a program so you can convert its data in a buffer of characters, a structure has been made for that.<br /><br />This is an example of such a file :<br />/* XPM */<br />static char * tilegrass2_16x16_xpm[] = {<br />&quot;16 16 8 1&quot;,<br />&quot;       c None&quot;,<br />&quot;.      c #406030&quot;,<br />&quot;+      c #688038&quot;,<br />&quot;@      c #2B471D&quot;,<br />&quot;#      c #80A820&quot;,<br />&quot;$      c #E0F830&quot;,<br />&quot;%      c #C0B060&quot;,<br />&quot;&amp;      c #908040&quot;,<br />&quot;.+.@.+.+@.+.@.+.&quot;,<br />&quot;.+#.+#.+@.+##.+.&quot;,<br />&quot;..##+.#+.+.#+.+#&quot;,<br />&quot;+..#@.+#.#.#$%.+&quot;,<br />&quot;.+.+#@.#.+.#%&amp;..&quot;,<br />&quot;.@.$$@.+#.@+.@+.&quot;,<br />&quot;+@@$%..+#.@@.@+.&quot;,<br />&quot;++.@@+@..@.@@...&quot;,<br />&quot;...#.+.@.+..@.#+&quot;,<br />&quot;+..+#.@@@..#+.++&quot;,<br />&quot;+++++.+++.++.+.@&quot;,<br />&quot;.+..+#++.##+.+.@&quot;,<br />&quot;..@..+.#.@$%..#+&quot;,<br />&quot;+#.@@@++.@%&amp;@.+.&quot;,<br />&quot;.+.+..+..@+@.++.&quot;,<br />&quot;..@.+.+.@+.+...@&quot;};<br /><br />Now my program just gives you something which can be made to a choice of NES image binary formats, you only have to convert from a character array as I said, pygame works this way also.<br /><br />Source code is at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://sf.net/projects/xpmnes">https://sf.net/projects/xpmnes</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If your NES incbins are full you can use my program for embedding xpm files just in plain C.<br /><br />HTH.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4707">erana</a> â€” Sat Apr 26, 2014 1:48 am</p><hr />
